- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper may involve distributed computing techniques for forensic analysis of IM and VoIP applications. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper discusses the impact of IM and VoIP applications on society and the need for forensic analysis in legal cases. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper may involve software engineering techniques for developing forensic tools for IM and VoIP applications. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper may discuss the usability and user experience of IM and VoIP applications in the context of forensic analysis.
